HEADWORD: Ferruginous
<hw>Fer*ru"gi*nous</hw> <pr>(f⟦ecr⟧r*r⟦udd⟧"j⟦icr⟧*n⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>ferruginus</ets>, <ets>ferrugineus</ets>,
fr. <ets>ferrugo</ets>, <ets>-ginis</ets>, iron rust: cf. F.
<ets>ferrugineux</ets>. See <er>Ferrugo</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Partaking of iron; containing particles of iron.</def>
<rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Resembling iron rust in appearance or color;
brownish red, or yellowish red.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ferrugo</ent>⟦br⟧
